{"lemma":"أَدِيمِ","slug":"أَدِيمِ","root":"#.د.م","root_slug":"_-د-م","root_link":"/words/roots/_-د-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n453"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n453","headword_ar":"اَدِيمٌ","root":"Adm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oduwmN","text_ar":"مَاْدُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seasoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAmN","text_ar":"طَعَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oduwmN","text_ar":"مَاْدُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seasoned food"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food in which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_idaAm","text_ar":"اـِدَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samonukumo huriyqa","text_ar":"سَمْنُكُمْ هُرِيقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^adiymikumo","text_ar":"فِى اَدِيمِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Your clarified butter is poured into your seasoned food"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, TA;) applied to a niggardly man; (Har p. 462;) meaning, your good, or wealth, returns unto you: (TA:) or, as some say, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into your"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaA='","text_ar":"سِقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, Har * ubi suprà:) and the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daqiyqikumo","text_ar":"دَقِيقِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into your flour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samonuhumo fiY A^adiymihimo","text_ar":"سَمْنُهُمْ فِى اَدِيمِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their clarified butter is in their seasoned food"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, their good, or wealth, returns unto them. (M.) And the saying of Khadeejeh to the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aka latakosibu","text_ar":"اـِنَّكَ لَتَكْسِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa tuToEimu AlmaA^oduwma","text_ar":"وَ تُطْعِمُ المَاْدُومَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEoduwma","text_ar":"المَعْدُومَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thou gainest what is denied to others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makest"},{"kind":"text","text":"others"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to gain what they have not, of the things they want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makest the poor to gain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Edm","text_ar":"عدم"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and givest to eat food in which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_idaAm","text_ar":"اـِدَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in the present art.) [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEamotuka","text_ar":"اَطْعَمْتُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oduwmiY","text_ar":"مَاْدُومِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuka biEu*oriY","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُكَ بِعُذْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave thee my excuse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my virginity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) [or,] as some say, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my good manners:"},{"kind":"text","text":"said by the wife of Dureyd Ibn-Es-Simmeh, on the occasion of his divorcing her. (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (Ham p. 205, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tanned skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hide; leather:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Ham, Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whatever state it be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hide, in the state after that in which it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afiyqN","text_ar":"اَفِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is, when it is complete"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its tanning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and has become red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exterior of the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (T:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=dimapN","text_ar":"ا=دِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=daAmN","text_ar":"ا=دَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^udumN","text_ar":"اُدُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) the last from Lh, and [says ISd] I hold that he who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rusolN","text_ar":"رُسْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^udomN","text_ar":"اُدْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adamN","text_ar":"اَدَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb, K,) or this is a quasi-pl. n., (Sb, M, Mgh,) [often used as a gen. n.,] of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=daAmN","text_ar":"ا=دَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be pl. (M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiboni A^adiymK","text_ar":"اِبْنِ اَدِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A^adiymayoni","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اَدِيمَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu valaAvapi A=dimapK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ ثَلَاثَةِ ا=دِمَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":". One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~amaA yuEaAtabu AlA^adiymu *uw Alba$arapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّمَا يُعَاتَبُ الاَدِيمُ ذُو البَشَرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Only the hide that has the exterior part, upon which the hair grows, is put again into the tan:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) a prov.; (TA;) meaning, only he is disciplined, or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":37},{"kind":"text","text":"reproved, who is an object of hope, and in whom is full intelligence, and strength; (T, TA, and AHn in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b$r","text_ar":"بشر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[where, however, in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna","text_ar":"دُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w","text_ar":"ذو"},{"kind":"text","text":"];) and only he is disputed with in whom is place for dispute. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adiymu AlHarobi","text_ar":"اَدِيمُ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used metaphorically for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adiymu","text_ar":"اَدِيمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholi AlHarobi","text_ar":"اَهْلِ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The skin of the warriors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the people engaged in war"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHiyHu AlA^adiymi","text_ar":"صَحِيحُ الاَدِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is sound of skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is sound in respect of origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 135.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN bariYo'u AlA^adiymi mim~aA luTixa bihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بَرِىْءُ الاَدِيمِ مِمَّا لُطِخَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is clear in honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation, of that with which he has been aspersed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, * TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maz~aqa A^adamiY","text_ar":"مَزَّقَ اَدَمِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rent my honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har ubi suprà.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adiymN","text_ar":"اَدِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surface"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the earth or ground: (S, M:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adamapN","text_ar":"اَدَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what appears"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof, (K,) and of the sky. (M, K.) ―         -b7-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the period called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuka A^adiyma AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"جِيْتُكَ اَدِيمَ الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee in the first part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DHY","text_ar":"ضحى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, M;) app. meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda A@rotifaAEi AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"عِنْدَ ا@رْتِفَاعِ الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the morning was becoming advanced; when the sun was becoming high"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b8-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of day: (IAar, M, K, TA:) and (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of night: (IAar, M, TA:) or (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the day, (M, A, K, TA,) and of the night. (A, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a A^adiyma Aln~ahaAri SaAy^imFA waA^adiyma All~ayoli qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ اَدِيمَ النَّهَارِ صَايِمًا وَاَدِيمَ اللَّيْلِ قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He continued the whole of the day fasting, and the whole of the night standing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in prayer, &c.]. (A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","TA","M","K","Ham","Mgh","Msb","S","Sb","IAar","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}